</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[506,586,1944,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[506,586,1944,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
2−5, habitus. Scale bars: 2−5 = 500μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption pageId="3" pageNumber="374" startId="3.[151,264,1026,1050]" targetBox="[151,1435,181,1002]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1026,1087]" pageId="3" pageNumber="374">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,330,1026,1050]" pageId="3" pageNumber="374">FIGURES 6−11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zhou &amp; Ma, 2022" authorityName="Zhou &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2022" box="[338,530,1027,1051]" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Willowsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifascia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[338,530,1027,1051]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Willowsia trifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[538,621,1027,1051]" pageId="3" pageNumber="374">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[538,621,1027,1051]" pageId="3" pageNumber="374" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
6, scale; 7, proximal part of antenna; 8, eyes; 9, distal part of manubrium and proximal part of dentes; 10, hind claw; 11, dorsal chaetotaxy of Abd. V. Scale bars: 6 = 10μm, 7−11 = 20μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1133,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="374">
Scales. Scales spinulate 
<typeStatus box="[474,522,1133,1159]" pageId="3" pageNumber="374">type</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[539,608,1133,1160]" captionStart="FIGURES 6−11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1026,1050]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1002]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1435,181,1003]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6−11. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 6, scale; 7, proximal part of antenna; 8, eyes; 9, distal part of manubrium and proximal part of dentes; 10, hind claw; 11, dorsal chaetotaxy of Abd. V. Scale bars: 6 = 10μm, 7−11 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), present on Ant. I−II (
<figureCitation box="[871,940,1133,1159]" captionStart="FIGURES 6−11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1026,1050]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1002]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1435,181,1003]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6−11. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 6, scale; 7, proximal part of antenna; 8, eyes; 9, distal part of manubrium and proximal part of dentes; 10, hind claw; 11, dorsal chaetotaxy of Abd. V. Scale bars: 6 = 10μm, 7−11 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), head (
<figureCitation box="[1032,1100,1133,1159]" captionStart="FIGURES 6−11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1026,1050]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1002]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1435,181,1003]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6−11. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 6, scale; 7, proximal part of antenna; 8, eyes; 9, distal part of manubrium and proximal part of dentes; 10, hind claw; 11, dorsal chaetotaxy of Abd. V. Scale bars: 6 = 10μm, 7−11 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), terga, legs, ventral tube and ventral side of manubrium. Basal part of ventral side of dens also with scales (
<figureCitation box="[1028,1097,1169,1195]" captionStart="FIGURES 6−11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1026,1050]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1002]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1435,181,1003]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6−11. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 6, scale; 7, proximal part of antenna; 8, eyes; 9, distal part of manubrium and proximal part of dentes; 10, hind claw; 11, dorsal chaetotaxy of Abd. V. Scale bars: 6 = 10μm, 7−11 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1133,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="374">
Head.Antennae 0.66−0.80 times body length; antennal segments ratio as I: II: III: IV = 1: 1.54−1.79: 1.23−1.57: 1.87−2.57. Distal part of Ant. IV with many sensory chaetae, normal ciliate chaetae and a bilobed apical bulb (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 12−19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,537,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[151,1436,525,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12−19. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 12, apex of Ant. IV; 13, distal part of Ant. III; 14, distal part of Ant. II; 15, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 16, labrum; 17, lateral process of labial palp; 18, labium; 19, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 12−19 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Distal part of Ant. III with 3−4 rods (
<figureCitation box="[630,715,1277,1303]" captionStart="FIGURES 12−19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,537,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[151,1436,525,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12−19. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 12, apex of Ant. IV; 13, distal part of Ant. III; 14, distal part of Ant. II; 15, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 16, labrum; 17, lateral process of labial palp; 18, labium; 19, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 12−19 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Distal part of Ant. II with 2−3 rods (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1238,1277,1303]" captionStart="FIGURES 12−19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,537,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[151,1436,525,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12−19. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 12, apex of Ant. IV; 13, distal part of Ant. III; 14, distal part of Ant. II; 15, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 16, labrum; 17, lateral process of labial palp; 18, labium; 19, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 12−19 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Dorsal cephalic chaetotaxy as 8−12 antennal (An), four median (M) and nine sutural (S) mac. Ps2 present. Interocular chaetae as p, s, t mes. Eyes 8+8, G and H smaller (
<figureCitation box="[571,643,1349,1375]" captionStart="FIGURES 6−11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1026,1050]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1002]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1435,181,1003]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6−11. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 6, scale; 7, proximal part of antenna; 8, eyes; 9, distal part of manubrium and proximal part of dentes; 10, hind claw; 11, dorsal chaetotaxy of Abd. V. Scale bars: 6 = 10μm, 7−11 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Figs 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[656,687,1349,1376]" captionStart="FIGURES 12−19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,537,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[151,1436,525,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12−19. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 12, apex of Ant. IV; 13, distal part of Ant. III; 14, distal part of Ant. II; 15, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 16, labrum; 17, lateral process of labial palp; 18, labium; 19, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 12−19 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">15</figureCitation>
). Prelabral and labral chaetae as 4/5, 5, 4, prelabral chaetae ciliate, other smooth, four labral papillae with one minute denticle each (
<figureCitation box="[871,954,1385,1412]" captionStart="FIGURES 12−19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,537,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[151,1436,525,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12−19. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 12, apex of Ant. IV; 13, distal part of Ant. III; 14, distal part of Ant. II; 15, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 16, labrum; 17, lateral process of labial palp; 18, labium; 19, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 12−19 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Lateral process (l. p.) of labial palp slightly curved, with tip not reaching apex of labial papilla (
<figureCitation box="[752,835,1421,1447]" captionStart="FIGURES 12−19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,537,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[151,1436,525,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12−19. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 12, apex of Ant. IV; 13, distal part of Ant. III; 14, distal part of Ant. II; 15, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 16, labrum; 17, lateral process of labial palp; 18, labium; 19, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 12−19 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Labial triangular chaetae usually as M1M2REL1L2, all ciliate and R 0.67−0.77 length of M1, rarely R duplicated (
<figureCitation box="[831,913,1457,1483]" captionStart="FIGURES 12−19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,537,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[151,1436,525,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12−19. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 12, apex of Ant. IV; 13, distal part of Ant. III; 14, distal part of Ant. II; 15, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 16, labrum; 17, lateral process of labial palp; 18, labium; 19, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 12−19 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Subapical chaeta of maxillary outer lobe thin, subequal to apical one; three smooth hairs on sublobal plate (
<figureCitation box="[836,919,1493,1519]" captionStart="FIGURES 12−19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,537,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-152@4.[151,1436,525,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12−19. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 12, apex of Ant. IV; 13, distal part of Ant. III; 14, distal part of Ant. II; 15, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 16, labrum; 17, lateral process of labial palp; 18, labium; 19, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 12−19 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1133,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="374">
Thorax. Th. II with three (m1, m2, m2i) mac on T1 area, seven (a5, m4, m4i, m4p, m5 and two unknown) mac on T2 area, 25−27 posterior mac, one ms and two se on each side. Th. III with 24−27, two se on each side (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1424,1565,1591]" captionStart="FIGURES 20−23" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1251,1275]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,188,1216]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,181,1227]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 20−23. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 20, chaetotaxy of Th. II−III; 21, coxal macrochaetal formula of fore leg; 22, coxal macrochaetal formula of middle leg; 23, coxal macrochaetal formula of hind leg. Scale bars: 20−23 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Pseudopores on coxa I−III as 2, 3−4 (rarely 6), 1, respectively (
<figureCitation box="[852,984,1601,1627]" captionStart="FIGURES 20−23" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1251,1275]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,188,1216]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,181,1227]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 20−23. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 20, chaetotaxy of Th. II−III; 21, coxal macrochaetal formula of fore leg; 22, coxal macrochaetal formula of middle leg; 23, coxal macrochaetal formula of hind leg. Scale bars: 20−23 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Figs 21−23</figureCitation>
). Trochanteral organ with 51−96 smooth spiny chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[317,401,1637,1663]" captionStart="FIGURES 24−26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1363,1387]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,190,1338]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[173,1414,181,1340]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 24−26. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 24, trochanteral organ; 25, hind foot complex; 26, chaetotaxy of Abd. I−III. Scale bars: 24−26 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Unguis with four inner teeth, one pair located 0.50−0.52 from base of inner edge of unguis, distal unpaired two respectively at 0.75−0.76 and 0.88−0.90 distance from base. Unguiculus acuminate and outer edge serrate. Tenent hair thick with its tip clavate, longer than inner side of unguis (
<figureCitation box="[1086,1173,1709,1735]" captionStart="FIGURES 6−11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1026,1050]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1002]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1435,181,1003]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6−11. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 6, scale; 7, proximal part of antenna; 8, eyes; 9, distal part of manubrium and proximal part of dentes; 10, hind claw; 11, dorsal chaetotaxy of Abd. V. Scale bars: 6 = 10μm, 7−11 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1185,1217,1709,1736]" captionStart="FIGURES 24−26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1363,1387]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,190,1338]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[173,1414,181,1340]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 24−26. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 24, trochanteral organ; 25, hind foot complex; 26, chaetotaxy of Abd. I−III. Scale bars: 24−26 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1133,2023]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,150,501]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="375" pageId="3" pageNumber="374">
Abdomen. Abd. IV 4.55−6.50 times as long as Abd. III along dorsal midline. Abd. I with seven (m2, m2i, m3, m4, a2, a3, a5) mac, one ms and one se, ms not inner to se. Abd. II with two (a2, a3) mac on A1 area, four (m3, m3e, m3ea, m3ep) mac on A2 area, one (m5) lateral mac and two se. Abd. III with two (a2, a3) mac on A4 area, one (m3) mac on A5 area, five (am6, pm6, p6, m7, p7) lateral mac, one ms and two se (
<figureCitation box="[1023,1108,1853,1880]" captionStart="FIGURES 24−26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1363,1387]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,190,1338]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[173,1414,181,1340]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 24−26. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 24, trochanteral organ; 25, hind foot complex; 26, chaetotaxy of Abd. I−III. Scale bars: 24−26 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Abd. IV with 16−20 central and 18−22 lateral mac (
<figureCitation box="[419,504,1889,1915]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,195,1582]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1436,181,1591]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 27. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 27, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV. Scale bar: 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Abd. V with three se (
<figureCitation box="[772,859,1889,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 6−11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1026,1050]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1002]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1435,181,1003]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6−11. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 6, scale; 7, proximal part of antenna; 8, eyes; 9, distal part of manubrium and proximal part of dentes; 10, hind claw; 11, dorsal chaetotaxy of Abd. V. Scale bars: 6 = 10μm, 7−11 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Figs 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[872,904,1889,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 28−34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,282,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-62@8.[151,1436,273,1883]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28−34. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 28, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 29, anterior face of ventral tube; 30, posterior face of ventral tube; 31, lateral flap of ventral tube; 32, manubrial plaque; 33, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 34, mucro. Scale bars: 28−34 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">28</figureCitation>
). Ventral tube anteriorly with sacles and 14−16 ciliate chaetae on each side, three of them much larger than others (
<figureCitation box="[918,1004,1925,1951]" captionStart="FIGURES 28−34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,282,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-62@8.[151,1436,273,1883]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28−34. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 28, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 29, anterior face of ventral tube; 30, posterior face of ventral tube; 31, lateral flap of ventral tube; 32, manubrial plaque; 33, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 34, mucro. Scale bars: 28−34 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); posteriorly with two smooth chaetae on apical part (
<figureCitation box="[325,411,1961,1987]" captionStart="FIGURES 28−34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,282,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-62@8.[151,1436,273,1883]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28−34. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 28, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 29, anterior face of ventral tube; 30, posterior face of ventral tube; 31, lateral flap of ventral tube; 32, manubrial plaque; 33, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 34, mucro. Scale bars: 28−34 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
); laterally with six smooth and 17 ciliate chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[991,1076,1961,1987]" captionStart="FIGURES 28−34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,282,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-62@8.[151,1436,273,1883]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28−34. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 28, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 29, anterior face of ventral tube; 30, posterior face of ventral tube; 31, lateral flap of ventral tube; 32, manubrial plaque; 33, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 34, mucro. Scale bars: 28−34 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Manubrial plate dorsally with 11−22 ciliate chaetae and 3−4 pseudopores (
<figureCitation box="[657,743,1997,2023]" captionStart="FIGURES 28−34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,282,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-62@8.[151,1436,273,1883]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28−34. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 28, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 29, anterior face of ventral tube; 30, posterior face of ventral tube; 31, lateral flap of ventral tube; 32, manubrial plaque; 33, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 34, mucro. Scale bars: 28−34 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
); ventrally with 34−43 ciliate chaetae on each side (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,1997,2023]" captionStart="FIGURES 28−34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,282,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-62@8.[151,1436,273,1883]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28−34. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 28, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 29, anterior face of ventral tube; 30, posterior face of ventral tube; 31, lateral flap of ventral tube; 32, manubrial plaque; 33, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 34, mucro. Scale bars: 28−34 = 20μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
). Uncrenulated dens 1.07−1.45 times as mucro in length. Mucro bidentate, two teeth subequal and tip of basal spine reaching subapical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[440,525,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 28−34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,282,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-62@8.[151,1436,273,1883]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28−34. Willowsia trifascia sp. nov. 28, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 29, anterior face of ventral tube; 30, posterior face of ventral tube; 31, lateral flap of ventral tube; 32, manubrial plaque; 33, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 34, mucro. Scale bars: 28−34 = 20μm." pageId="4" pageNumber="375">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="375" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,223,249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">Ecology.</emphasis>
Found in rotten leaf, mainly composed of 
<taxonomicName box="[775,982,223,249]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tabuliformis">
<emphasis box="[775,982,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">Pinus tabuliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[996,1245,223,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="liaotungensis">
<emphasis box="[996,1245,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">Quercus liaotungensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zabelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">Cotoneaster zabelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,828,295,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,501]" box="[199,828,295,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after its three bands on dorsal body.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="375" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species can be distinguished from other known 
<taxonomicName box="[996,1199,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">
<emphasis box="[996,1106,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">Willowsia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
because of its three longitudinal blue stripes on dorsal body. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhou, Pan &amp; Ma, 2021" authorityName="Zhou, Pan &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2021" box="[784,1152,367,393]" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Willowsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis box="[784,876,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">W. flava</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zhou, R. &amp; Pan, Z. X. &amp; Ma, Y. T." box="[884,1152,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" pagination="73 - 92" refId="ref7221" refString="Zhou, R., Pan, Z. X. &amp; Ma, Y. T. (2021) Three new species Willowsia (Collembola: Entomobryidae) from China and notes on W. japonica. Zootaxa, 4991 (1), 73 - 92. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4991.1.3" type="journal article" year="2021">Zhou, Pan &amp; Ma, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(in: 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhou, R. &amp; Pan, Z. X. &amp; Ma, Y. T." box="[1195,1388,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" pagination="73 - 92" refId="ref7221" refString="Zhou, R., Pan, Z. X. &amp; Ma, Y. T. (2021) Three new species Willowsia (Collembola: Entomobryidae) from China and notes on W. japonica. Zootaxa, 4991 (1), 73 - 92. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4991.1.3" type="journal article" year="2021">
Zhou 
<emphasis box="[1262,1313,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Martynova, 1972" authorityName="Martynova" authorityYear="1972" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Willowsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="samarkandica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">W. samarkandica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martynova, E. F." box="[317,510,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" pagination="147 - 150" refId="ref6628" refString="Martynova, E. F. (1972) Springtails (Collembola) inhabiting the outlets of Subterranean water in the Kirghiz and Uzbek SSR. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the USSR Academy of Sciences, 51, 147 - 150." type="journal article" year="1972">Martynova, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ma, 2016" authorityName="Ma" authorityYear="2016" box="[565,823,403,429]" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Willowsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[565,707,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="375">W. variabilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ma, Y. T." box="[715,823,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" pagination="137 - 145" refId="ref6542" refString="Ma, Y. T. (2016) Two new species of Willowsia (Collembola: Entomobryidae) from Guizhou Province, China. Zootaxa, 4158 (1), 137 - 145. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4158.1.9" type="journal article" year="2016">
Ma, 
<quantity box="[767,823,403,429]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.12064" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" unit="in" value="2016.0">2016</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in macrochaetotaxy of body. However, there are some differences between them, such as, colour pattern, sculpture and distribution of scales, macrochaetotaxy of head and Th. II−III, apical bulb of Ant. IV and mucro (
<tableCitation box="[658,741,475,501]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,239,1359,1383]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparision between W. trifascia sp. nov. and its similar species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF3E664EFFC0FFBE1593FA83D1BCFAE0" pageId="4" pageNumber="375" tableUuid="DF3E664EFFC0FFBE1593FA83D1BCFAE0">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
